{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"709ffe28-3721-44f9-910a-191800b3c0cd","content":"I can help you analyze a .NET crash dump! Let me check what tools are available and look for your dump file.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VRuusxDd9ELtmDRBT4F2L1","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Analyzing .NET crash dump"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01L2KwPu4SDrNxPS6fvXAPee","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"which dotnet 2>/dev/null && dotnet --version 2>/dev/null; which dotnet-dump 2>/dev/null; which lldb 2>/dev/null; ls *.dmp 2>/dev/null || echo \"No .dmp files in current directory\"","description":"Check available tools and dump files","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check available tools and dump files"}],"interactionId":"c3dd762d-c3d0-419d-b3ea-5b9ec06170b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and approaches are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see:\n- `dump-collect` - but this is for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is not appropriate here. Let me think about what I can help with directly.\n\nFor analyzing .NET crash dumps, the typical tools are:\n- `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n\n\n- `lldb` with SOS plugin (Linux)\n- WinDbg with SOS (Windows)\n\nSince the user already has the file, I should ask them where it's located and help them use `dotnet-dump analyze` to examine it, or guide them through the analysis process if they can share the dump with me.","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"D807:3A9384:20E464:26AF39:69F2B6AA"},"id":"4fe482a5-8b4c-44e4-808a-24925c259104","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:56:06.999Z","parentId":"fc8860b5-059c-47b5-8e4a-dd388ea2c074"}
